# file-guard.conf — one glob pattern per line.
#
# Copy this to .claude/file-guard.conf (project) or ~/.claude/file-guard.conf
# (global). The hook uses the FIRST config it finds; there is no merging.
#
# Rules:
#   - Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
#   - Leading/trailing whitespace is trimmed.
#   - `~/` at the start of a pattern expands to your home directory.
#   - A pattern CONTAINING a slash matches the full absolute path; if it is
#     relative (no leading / or ~/), it matches at any depth.
#   - A pattern WITHOUT a slash matches the basename anywhere.
#   - Matching is case-insensitive by default (set FILE_GUARD_CASE_SENSITIVE=1
#     to opt out).
#   - `*` in a pattern crosses `/` boundaries, so `secrets/*` already matches
#     nested files like `secrets/prod/db.pem`. You do NOT need `secrets/**`.

# --- Recommended: protect the guard itself from being disarmed ---------------
# Without these, the agent could edit the config or the hook wiring to turn the
# guard off. Adding them is not a hard lock (see README "What it does NOT do"),
# but it makes disarming a visible, blocked action instead of a silent one.
~/.claude/file-guard.conf
.claude/file-guard.conf
.claude/settings.json

# --- Credentials and keys ----------------------------------------------------
.env
*.pem
*.key
id_rsa
id_ed25519

# --- Whole directories -------------------------------------------------------
# secrets/*
# ~/Documents/private/*
